This article discusses the theoretical-methodological advances of the communication and work research from the reception studies. It also discusses the necessity to deepen the developed research realized until now, taking as problem the subjectivity and the communication relations. So, this article proposes to discuss, in an introductory way, the contributions that it is possible to reach utilizing the cross-disciplinary theoretical approach of Ergology. The Ergology studies work as a human activity that holds norms and their transformation by means of the real work. The communication relations have determinative role in the accomplishment of the activity of work.